---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import Trace from "../../components/Trace.astro";
import ConceptTags from "../../components/ConceptTags.astro";
import DocTable from "../../components/DocTable.astro";
import { Code } from "astro:components";

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;

const rulesFile = `require lint before deploy
require human-approval before deploy
limit deploy to 3 per session`;

const serverCode = `import { createPetriflowFactory } from "@petriflow/vercel-ai";
import { streamText, tool } from "ai";
import { openai } from "@ai-sdk/openai";
import { z } from "zod";
import { Hono } from "hono";

// 1. Compile once at startup
const factory = await createPetriflowFactory("./safety.rules", {
  mode: "enforce",
  onDecision: (event, decision) => {
    if (decision?.block) {
      console.warn(\`[BLOCKED] \${event.toolName}: \${decision.reason}\`);
    }
  },
});

console.log(\`Loaded \${factory.nets.length} nets\`);

// 2. Define tools (shared across all requests)
const myTools = {
  lint: tool({
    description: "Run the linter",
    inputSchema: z.object({}),
    execute: async () => ({ passed: true }),
  }),
  deploy: tool({
    description: "Deploy to production",
    inputSchema: z.object({ version: z.string() }),
    execute: async ({ version }) => ({ deployed: version }),
  }),
};

const app = new Hono();

// 3. Per request — fresh session
app.post("/chat", async (c) => {
  const gate = factory.createSession();

  const result = streamText({
    model: openai("gpt-4o"),
    tools: gate.wrapTools(myTools),
    system: gate.systemPrompt(),
    prompt: await c.req.text(),
  });

  return result.toTextStreamResponse();
});

export default app;`;

const withoutFactory = `// Without factory — works, but easy to get wrong
const { nets } = await loadRules("./safety.rules");

app.post("/chat", async (c) => {
  // Easy to accidentally lift this out of the handler
  const gate = createPetriflowGate(nets, {
    mode: "enforce",
    onDecision: (event, decision) => { /* ... */ },
  });
  // ...
});`;

const withFactory = `// With factory — lifecycle is explicit
const factory = await createPetriflowFactory("./safety.rules", {
  mode: "enforce",
  onDecision: (event, decision) => { /* ... */ },
});

app.post("/chat", async (c) => {
  const gate = factory.createSession();
  // ...
});`;

const inlineRules = `// Inline rules — no .rules file needed
const factory = await createPetriflowFactory({
  rules: \`
    require lint before deploy
    limit deploy to 3 per session
  \`,
});`;

const precompiled = `// Pre-compiled nets — skip the file read
import { compile } from "@petriflow/rules";

const { nets } = compile("require lint before deploy");
const factory = await createPetriflowFactory({ nets });`;

const installCmd = `bun add @petriflow/vercel-ai @petriflow/rules ai @ai-sdk/openai zod hono`;
---
<Layout title="Server Integration | PetriFlow" description="Integrate PetriFlow into a multi-user server. Compile rules once at startup, create fresh sessions per request.">
  <Nav currentPage="docs" />

  <div class="doc-wrapper">
    <div class="page-header">
      <div class="tutorial-heading">
        <h1>Server Integration</h1>
      </div>
      <ConceptTags concepts={["Session factory", "Per-request isolation", "Server integration", "Streaming responses"]} />
      <p>Integrate PetriFlow into a multi-user server. <strong>Compile rules once at startup</strong>, <strong>create fresh sessions per request</strong>. You'll learn the factory pattern, per-request isolation, and multiple input formats.</p>
    </div>

    <aside class="doc-sidebar" aria-label="Page navigation">
      <nav class="doc-nav">
        <a href="#what-youll-build">What you'll build</a>
        <a href="#prerequisites">Prerequisites</a>
        <a href="#the-problem">The problem</a>
        <a href="#the-factory-pattern">The factory pattern</a>
        <a href="#full-server">Full server</a>
        <a href="#input-formats">Input formats</a>
        <a href="#concepts">Concepts</a>
        <a href="#next-steps">Next steps</a>
      </nav>
    </aside>

    <main id="main-content">

    <div class="doc-section" id="what-youll-build">
      <h2>What you'll build</h2>
      <p>An HTTP server where every request gets its own gated agent session. Rules compile once at startup. Each request gets fresh marking state — one user's progress never leaks into another's.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-section" id="prerequisites">
      <h2>Prerequisites</h2>
      <Code code={installCmd} lang="bash" />
      <p>You'll also need an API key for your model provider. This tutorial assumes you've read <a href={`${base}docs/tutorial-file-safety/`} style="color:var(--accent-text)">Tutorial 1: File Safety</a> and <a href={`${base}docs/tutorial-deployment/`} style="color:var(--accent-text)">Tutorial 2: Deployment Agent</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-section" id="the-problem">
      <h2>The problem</h2>
      <p>In a single-request script, you create one gate and use it once. In a server, you need fresh state per request — but the compiled rules are the same every time. The naive approach works but is fragile:</p>
      <Code code={withoutFactory} lang="typescript" />
      <p>The compiled nets are immutable, but the gate holds mutable state: markings, deferred transitions, rate-limit budgets. If someone refactors the gate creation out of the handler for "performance", all users share one set of markings. Rate limits become global. Sequencing breaks across requests.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-section" id="the-factory-pattern">
      <h2>The factory pattern</h2>
      <Code code={withFactory} lang="typescript" />
      <p><code>createPetriflowFactory</code> captures the compiled nets and options once. <code>createSession()</code> returns a fresh <code>PetriflowGate</code> with independent state. The lifecycle is explicit: one factory = one rule set, one session = one user's markings.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-section" id="full-server">
      <h2>Full server</h2>
      <p>Write the rules file:</p>
      <div class="example-rule" set:html={`<span class="comment"># safety.rules</span>
<span class="kw">require</span> <span class="str">lint</span> before <span class="str">deploy</span>
<span class="kw">require</span> <span class="str">human-approval</span> before <span class="str">deploy</span>
<span class="kw">limit</span> <span class="str">deploy</span> to <span class="str">3</span> per <span class="str">session</span>`} />

      <p>Wire it up:</p>
      <Code code={serverCode} lang="typescript" />
      <p>Each POST to <code>/chat</code> gets its own gate session. The factory compiles <code>safety.rules</code> once. <code>gate.systemPrompt()</code> tells the model about the constraints. <code>gate.wrapTools()</code> instruments each tool. Blocked calls throw <code>ToolCallBlockedError</code>, which the Vercel AI SDK feeds back to the model as a tool error.</p>

      <Trace label="// Two users, independent sessions" steps={[
        { icon: "ok", html: `User A calls <strong>lint()</strong><br><span class="ok-text">OK</span> Session A advances: deploy now reachable` },
        { icon: "blocked", html: `User B calls <strong>deploy()</strong><br><span class="blocked-text">BLOCKED</span> Session B is fresh — lint hasn't run in this session` },
        { icon: "ok", html: `User A calls <strong>deploy()</strong><br><span class="ok-text">ALLOWED</span> Session A: lint done, deploy permitted` },
        { icon: "ok", html: `User B calls <strong>lint()</strong> then <strong>deploy()</strong><br><span class="ok-text">ALLOWED</span> Session B completes its own pipeline independently` },
      ]} />
    </div>

    <div class="doc-section" id="input-formats">
      <h2>Input formats</h2>
      <p>The factory accepts four input formats:</p>
      <Code code={inlineRules} lang="typescript" />
      <Code code={precompiled} lang="typescript" />
      <p>The string and <code>{'{ rules }'}</code> forms dynamically import <code>@petriflow/rules</code>. The <code>{'{ nets }'}</code> form works with any pre-compiled nets.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-section" id="concepts">
      <h2>Concepts</h2>
      <DocTable borderless rows={[
        ["Session factory", "Compile once, create fresh sessions on demand. <code>createPetriflowFactory</code> &rarr; <code>factory.createSession()</code>"],
        ["Per-request isolation", "Each session has independent markings, deferred tracking, and rate-limit budgets. No shared mutable state."],
        ["Immutable nets", "Compiled rule nets are structurally immutable. The factory captures them once and shares them across all sessions."],
      ]} />
    </div>

    <div class="doc-section" id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next steps</h2>
      <DocTable borderless rows={[
        [`<a href="${base}docs/vercel-ai/#session-factory">Session factory API reference</a>`, "Full API docs for <code>createPetriflowFactory</code> and <code>createSession</code>."],
        [`<a href="${base}docs/vercel-ai/#shadow-mode">Shadow mode</a>`, "Audit decisions before enforcing them in production."],
        [`<a href="${base}docs/vercel-ai/#registry-mode">Registry mode</a>`, "Dynamic rule activation for multi-tenant servers."],
      ]} />
    </div>

    </main>
  </div>

  <Footer variant="minimal" />
</Layout>
